ng/Tailoring skills or by taking the item to an NPC to repair).  I'm not too sure about the class system either - guess I'll have to see how it fleshes out, but at the moment it sounds awfully homogenous.<br>
<br>
The tentative release date is October 2003 - knowing how on the mark those types of dates are, I wouldn't expect to see the game hit the shelves until mid-2004 at the earliest.  Guess whether I play or not will really depend on where my life is and what the state of the current EQ game is like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utemperanceds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Temperance DS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#0000FF>(4/24/02 9:55:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ2</span><hr size=1> i'm not worried about this comming out too soon.  the date is set for october 2003 but i'm thinking closer to summer 2004.  this looks like a huge project..and with planes of power comming next christmas i think they'd want to give themselves a bit if time for that expansion to cool off before they take away from this game's player base.<br>
